==English==
===Etymology===
German ''hamster''

=== Pronunciation ===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /'hæmstəɽ/

=== Noun ===
'''hamster''' ([[hamsters]])

#''(Zoölogy):'' A small, short-tailed European [[rodent]], ''[[Cricetus]] [[frumentarius]]''. It is remarkable for having a pouch on each side of the jaw, under the skin, and for its migrations. -- often kept as a pet 
#:'''Example'''
#:*It was the cutest sight to see your '''hamster''' stuff his cheeks all puffy with his seed food, where was he going to store it?.

